ExecDesc.value: Microsoft Excel MergeCells Record Parsing Memory Corruption(IPV6 Version)

EngDesc.value: A code execution vulnerability exists in Microsoft Office Excel. The vulnerability is due to a boundary error when parsing MergeCells Excel records, which could lead to memory corruption. A remote, unauthenticated attacker could exploit this vulnerability by enticing a target user to open a crafted Excel document. A successful exploitation attempt may result in the execution of arbitrary code in the security context of the target user.
